@node "Requirements" "Requirements          "
@next "InstallUse"
@{b}@{u}What do you need to use FileSplit&Join?@{ub}@{uu}

 * Amiga with Kickstart 3.x

 This programm is tested on A1200 and A4000.

 Send all bugs to Author.

 Use that program on you own risk.

@endnode

@node "InstallUse" "Installation and Usage"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Requirements"
@{b}Here's how you install FileSplit&Join onto your system:@{ub}

 @{b}1)@{ub} Copy FileS&J and Guide in some directory.

 @{b}2)@{ub} Click twise on FileS&J icon.
 
 Usage:(Split)

 @{b}1)@{ub} Select input file by hands or press S button to the right
             of string gadget InFile: .

 @{b}2)@{ub} Select output dir.

 @{b}3)@{ub} Select output files size and dimension.
             Bytes - Size in bytes.
             KB    - Size in KB
             KiloB _ Size equal 1000*input number.

 @{b}4)@{ub} Press Start button.

 @{b}5)@{ub} If in Message window exists only Abort button then
             error is occured.

             1)Input File does'n exist.

             2)Out Dir does'n exists.

             3)Numbers of input files = 1 or >10000.

             4)Cannot allocate free memory.

 Usage:(Join)

 @{b}1)@{ub} Select first file (name must be x.0000).

 @{b}2)@{ub} Select output dir.
 
 @{b}3)@{ub} Press Start button.

@endnode

